# Linear-Style Modal Design Pattern

Use this compact, professional Linear-style design for all modals in the application.

## Modal Container
```tsx
<div className="fixed inset-0 z-50 bg-black bg-opacity-30 transition-opacity" onClick={onClose}>
  <div 
    className="fixed right-0 top-0 h-full w-full max-w-xl bg-white shadow-2xl transform transition-transform duration-300 ease-out overflow-y-auto"
    onClick={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}
    style={{ transform: isOpen ? 'translateX(0)' : 'translateX(100%)' }}
  >
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

## Form Structure
```tsx
<div className="flex flex-col h-full">
  {/* Header */}
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-3 border-b border-gray-200">
    <h2 className="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Modal Title</h2>
    <button onClick={onClose} className="p-1.5 text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded transition-colors">
      <X className="w-4 h-4" />
    </button>
